Description: Rubber of coarse red quartzite, roughly rectangular, all surfaces and edges smoothed or rounded.
Curator's comments: Found in a hole together with 9 sickle blades and a large bone needle (see EA 59710-59717), possibly all originally within a leather bag.
Bibliographic references: Brunton & Caton-Thompson 1928 / The Badarian Civilisation and Predynastic Remains near Badari (p. 17; pl. xxix.4)
Acquisition name: Donated by: British School of Archaeology, Egypt
